=== assistant text ===
The M486 commands in Prusa firmware are used for object management. The key lines are:

- `M486 AEmbossed text` — This sets the name/label of the current object to "Embossed text"
- `M486 AShape-Box` — This sets another object's name to "Shape-Box"

The text that will be shown on the print is **"Embossed text"**. This is a Prusa Slicer-generated gcode file where the object being printed is named "Embossed text" — it's an embossing operation (printing text raised on the surface of an existing object).

